1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new chapter to title 54 of the North Dakota Century
2 Code, relating to the creation of the North Dakota Ireland trade commission; and to provide for a
3 legislative management report.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. A new chapter to title 54 of the North Dakota Century Code is created and
6 enacted as follows:
7 North Dakota Ireland trade commission - Membership .
8 1. The North Dakota Ireland trade commission s shall :
9 a. Advance bilateral trade and investment between the state and Ireland;
10 b. Initiate joint action on issues of mutual interest to the state and Ireland;
11 c. Promote business and academic exchanges between the state and Ireland;
12 d. Encourage mutual economic support between the state and Ireland;
13 e. Encourage mutual investment in the infrastructure of the state and Ireland; and
14 f. Address any other issues deemed to be of mutual benefit to the state and
15 Ireland.
16 2. The North Dakota Ireland trade commission consists of :
17 a. Two members of the senate, appointed by the president pro tempore of the
18 senate;
19 b. Two members of the house of representatives, appointed by the speaker of the
20 house;
21 c. The executive director of the North Dakota trade office;
22 d. An individual knowledgeable of and interested in the promotion of international
23 trade, appointed by the executive director of the North Dakota trade office; and
24 e. The agriculture commissioner, or the commissioner's designee.
