1 3. Each appointed member shall serve for a term of two years. If a position becomes
2 vacant, the position must be filled for the duration of the term in the same manner as
3 the original appointment.
4 4. At the initial meeting of the commission and annually thereafter, the members shall
5 select one from among the four appointed legislators to serve as the chair.
6 Administration - Meetings - Reimbursement.
7 1. The North Dakota trade office shall provide administrative services to the North
8 Dakota Ireland trade commission and compensation under subsection 3 .
9 2. The commission shall meet two to four times per year, as deemed necessary by the
10 chair, at the call of the chair.
11 3. Each member of the North Dakota Ireland trade commission may be reimbursed upon
12 request for necessary expenses incurred in the performance of the member's duties at
13 the rate provided for members of the legislative assembly under subsection 1 o f
14 section 54 - 03 - 20 .
15 Report to legislative management.
16 On or before September first of each year, the North Dakota Ireland trade commission shal l
17 provide a report to the legislative management. The report must include:
18 1. A description of the commission's work;
19 2. A description of benefits to the state, and to sectors involved in international trade,
20 attributable to the commission's efforts;
21 3. Recommendations for legislation that would support trade between the state and
22 Ireland; and
23 4. A summary of anticipated commission activities in the following year.
